Thanks @pranavSharma  I am using  CUDA, GraphOptimizationLevel- ORT_ENABLE_BASIC ,ExecutionMode- ORT_SEQUENTIAL
  Code For Reference:-
    g_ort->SetIntraOpNumThreads(session_options, 1);
    g_ort->SetSessionGraphOptimizationLevel(session_options, ORT_ENABLE_BASIC);
    OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_CUDA(session_options, 0);

@anirudha16101, I still can't repo the case you encountered. I run with different models, like the FasterRCNN, ssd, tf_inception_resnet_v2, etc. I also use one session for multiple input data. I also dumped the cudaMalloc vs cudaFree withe the addresses, and found out that there's no memory leak for the memory allocated from our allocator. I'm not sure whether it related to your model, maybe some for some special operators. Is it possible to share your model with us?
You can also have a try with our test tool onnxruntime_perf_test.exe if you build it from source. Here's a guide for the tool: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/docs/ONNX_Runtime_Perf_Tuning.md
Last, for your model A & B, is it possible it merge it into one model? It could save data copy across device.
